gomodel:SYNGO_93  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using well characterized antibodies, it is demonstrated that RIM1 is present at the active zone. A knockout control is provided.. Experimental description: The quadruple homozygote floxed mice for RIM1αβ, RIM2αβγ, ELKS1α, and ELKS2α were generated by crossing single conditional knockout mice (Kaeser et al., 2008, Kaeser et al., 2009, Kaeser et al., 2011 and Liu et al., 2014)." ;
